    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I don't think exposing the stack depth is a good abstraction. `tx.origin` exists because it is an extra special address, it's the one that signed the transaction (it's attached to `tx`, not `msg`).\n\nI strongly believe you don't need anything more than the sender abstraction, and anymore more introduces very unintuitive behavior which could be exploitable\n",
